HEADWORD: cataclinal
<hw>cataclinal</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <fld>(Geol)</fld> <def>running in
the direction of the dip in surrounding rock strata; -- of valleys and
rivers. Opposite of <ant>anaclinal</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
